Build a clean, professional React frontend for a web application called 
“Maverick Certify – Certification Management Platform”.

The application should support the following screens and behavior:

**<strong>1. Authentication & Role Handling</strong>
<strong>- Simple login screen</strong>
<strong>- Roles: Admin, Certification Coordinator</strong>
<strong>- Role-based navigation visibility**</strong>

2. Dashboard (Main Screen)
- Show summary cards:
  - Total certificates generated
  - Emails sent
  - LinkedIn posts completed
  - Pending actions
- Show recent certification batches
- Color-coded status indicators

3. Certification Batch Management
- Create batch form:
  - Event/Training Name
  - Batch ID
  - Event Date

**<strong>- Display batch lifecycle:</strong>
<strong>  - Draft</strong>
<strong>  - Certificates Generated</strong>
<strong>  - Emails Sent</strong>
<strong>  - Completed</strong>
<strong>- Disable invalid actions based on status</strong>

<strong>4. Candidate Excel Upload</strong>
<strong>- Upload Excel file</strong>
<strong>- Show validation results:</strong>
<strong>  - Missing fields</strong>
<strong>  - Duplicate emails</strong>
<strong>  - Invalid email formats</strong>
<strong>- Prevent submission until errors are resolved</strong>

<strong>5. Certificate Template Management</strong>
<strong>- Upload or create certificate template</strong>
<strong>- Configure placeholders:</strong>
<strong>  - Candidate Name</strong>
<strong>  - Event Name</strong>
<strong>  - Date</strong>
<strong>  - Signatory Name</strong>
<strong>  - Signature Image</strong>
<strong>  - Logo</strong>
<strong>  - QR Code</strong>
<strong>- Preview template before saving</strong>
<strong>- Reuse templates across batches</strong>

<strong>6. Certificate Generation Screen</strong>
<strong>- Button to generate certificates</strong>
<strong>- Progress indicator</strong>
<strong>- Show success/failure count</strong>
<strong>- Confirmation dialog before re-generation**</strong>

7. Email Distribution Screen
- Customize email subject and body
- Send bulk emails
**<strong>- Show email status per candidate:</strong>
<strong>  - Grey: Not Sent</strong>
<strong>  - Blue: Sent</strong>
<strong>  - Green: Delivered / Opened**</strong>

8. LinkedIn Tracking Screen
- Show list of candidates with LinkedIn status
- Allow manual LinkedIn post URL submission
**<strong>- Status colors:</strong>
<strong>  - Red: Not Posted</strong>
<strong>  - Orange: Reminder Sent</strong>
<strong>  - Green: Posted</strong>
<strong>- Show reminder history</strong>

<strong>9. Reports & Downloads</strong>
<strong>- Batch-wise reports</strong>
<strong>- Email delivery report</strong>
<strong>- LinkedIn compliance report</strong>
<strong>- Export as Excel or PDF</strong>

<strong>10. Admin Screens</strong>
<strong>- Audit log viewer</strong>
<strong>- System configuration (email settings)</strong>
<strong>- User management</strong>

<strong>UI Guidelines:</strong>
<strong>- Clean, modern layout</strong>
<strong>- Use cards, tables, progress bars, and icons</strong>
<strong>- Responsive design</strong>
<strong>- Clear visual feedback for actions and errors</strong>
<strong>- No payment integrations**</strong>

The frontend should be API-driven and ready to connect to a FastAPI backend.
